news.title: Ambuja Cements to merge Sanghi Industries and Penna Cement with itself
news.para: Ambuja Cements will issue 12 equity shares of the face value of Rs 2 each for every 100 equity shares of Sanghi Industries of face value Rs. 10 each.

news.title: Sebi orders forensic audit of TARC's financial statements
news.para: TARC said that it shall provide all necessary information, assistance and cooperation concerning the forensic audit and shall inform the exchanges of any further developments in the matter.

news.title: Supreme court issues landmark directives to curb illegal constructions
news.para: A bench comprising Justices J B Pardiwala and R Mahadevan said even the post-construction violations must trigger swift corrective action, including demolition of the illegal part and penalties for erring officials.

news.title: Maharashtra government to revise proposal for vertical property cards
news.para: The proposed card will serve as a comprehensive document containing crucial details such as ownership rights, carpet area measurement, and information about bank loan secured against the property.

news.title: West Bengal government launches 'Banglar Bari' housing scheme
news.para: West Bengal Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee said that over 28 lakh genuine beneficiaries were identified in a survey conducted by the state for the 'Banglar Bari' scheme for which a total of Rs 1.2 lakh would be transferred to them by next December.

news.title: No action against homes in Hyderabad built before July 2024: HYDRAA
news.para: HYDRAA commissioner AV Ranganath, however, clarified that the exemption will not extend to commercial complexes built without proper approvals.

news.title: SC asks Greater Noida authority to submit a proposal for grievance redressal
news.para: The bench said it may order a CBI probe into the whole "mess" if the GNIDA did not come up with a plan to redress the grievances of the homebuyers.

news.title: NCLAT dismisses Spaze Towers' plea to limit insolvency process to single project
news.para: The National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT), on October 21, 2024, directed the initiation of insolvency proceedings against Spaze Towers, admitting a plea filed by its flat owners.

news.title: Gujarat RERA to simplify project progress reporting system for developers
news.para: The amendments, effective Jan 1, 2025, will bring significant changes aimed at streamlining compliance and improving project monitoring.

news.title: Tripura plans to establish three satellite towns: CM
news.para: Before departing for the Northeast Trade and Investment roadshow in Mumbai, Saha said while laying the foundation for seven development initiatives in Gomati district that the govt has earmarked Rs 27,000 crore in this year's budget for infrastructure and public amenity development.

news.title: Germany's property sector seen improvement in 2024
news.para: Global real estate firm Jones Lang LaSalle (JLL) predicted that property transactions in Germany would rise to 35 billion euros ($37 billion) in 2024 and increase further to between 40 billion and 42 billion euros in 2025.

news.title: Birla Estates acquires land parcel for Rs 104.3 crore in Boisar, Maharashtra
news.para: Previously, Birla Estates had bought around 24.5 acre land in Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR) for Rs 537.42 crore.

news.title: Embassy REIT raises Rs 1,000 crore through debt-refinancing
news.para: Embassy REIT will utilize the proceeds from this debt raise to repay its certain existing debt. Through this refinance, it will be able to secure c.70 basis points interest savings from the existing rate.

news.title: Mumbai: Retired government official arrested in multi-crore land scam in Malad
news.para: The arrested accused, Devdas Jairam Jadhav (64), is the third to be apprehended by a special investigation team of the crime branch set up by the high court to look into the alleged forged documents involving the City Land Survey Office,

news.title: ITC Hotels demerger to come into effect from January 1, 2025
news.para: Earlier in October this year, the Kolkata bench of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) approved the demerger between ITC Limited and ITC Hotels Limited.

news.title: House prices in UK likely to rise by 2-4% in 2025: Nationwide
news.para: From April first-time homebuyers in England will pay stamp duty on property costing 300,000 pounds ($379,320.00), rather than 425,000 pounds. Other buyers will have to pay tax from 125,000 pounds.

news.title: Government to reclaim unused industrial land: Industries minister, Telangana
news.para: Industries minister D Sridhar Babu revealed that a three-member committee of officials had been formed to assess whether industries are using the land for its intended purpose or for other activities.

news.title: Up line of Kolkata metro's airport stretch to be complete by January-end
news.para: Metro Railway, which is implementing the city's Yellow Line, aims to complete the second set of tracks by Jan, officials said.

news.title: No proposal to include additional cities in Smart Cities Mission: Centre
news.para: The government was asked whether it has any plan to select and develop another 100 new cities as Smart Cities apart from those 100 Smart Cities which were selected earlier.

news.title: Over 75 acres of land acquired across 82 plots for Patna rail metro project
news.para: Reviewing the land acquisition and transfer to the ambitious project here, the DM said Rs 255.93 crore was paid to 268 landowners, and an amount of Rs 124.72 crore was deposited with the authority as per the provisions.
